The paper discusses a technique for information concealing, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The technique is based on the concept of repeats in DNA, which suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT). The use of families of repeats also implies a potential application of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.CC). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a new approach to protecting sensitive content.
